<h2 id="Syntax-Difference"><a href="#Syntax-Difference" class="headerlink" title="Syntax Difference"></a>Syntax Difference</h2><h3 id="if-else-in-MATLAB"><a href="#if-else-in-MATLAB" class="headerlink" title="if-else in MATLAB"></a>if-else in MATLAB</h3><figure class="highlight matlab"><table><tr><td class="code"><pre><span class="line">a = <span class="number">100</span>;</span><br><span class="line">b = <span class="number">200</span>;</span><br><span class="line">   <span class="keyword">if</span>( a == <span class="number">100</span> )</span><br><span class="line"> </span><br><span class="line">       <span class="keyword">if</span>( b == <span class="number">200</span> )</span><br><span class="line">        </span><br><span class="line">          fprintf(<span class="string">'Value of a is 100 and b is 200 \n'</span> );</span><br><span class="line">       <span class="keyword">end</span></span><br><span class="line">       </span><br><span class="line">   <span class="keyword">end</span></span><br><span class="line">   fprintf(<span class="string">'Exact value of a is : %d '</span>, a, <span class="string">'\n'</span>);</span><br><span class="line">   fprintf(<span class="string">'Exact value of b is : %d'</span>, b );</span><br></pre></td></tr></table></figure>
